text:
Case 1: f(x) := x-5*y; (y is parameter)

L{f(x)} = int(exp(-s*x)*f(x),x=0..infinity);
L{f(x)} = int(exp(-s*x)*(x-5*y),x=0..infinity);
L{f(x)} = 1/s^2-5*y/s;

Case 2: f(y) := x-5*y; (x is parameter)

L{f(y)} = int(exp(-s*y)*f(y),y=0..infinity);
L{f(y)} = int(exp(-s*y)*(x-5*y),y=0..infinity);
L{f(y)} = x/s-5/s^2;

adv_text:
Case 1: f(tenth) := x-5*y; (y is parameters)

L{f(x)} = int(exp(-s*x)*f(x),x=0..infinity);
L{f(x)} = int(exp(-s*x)*(x-5*y),x=0..infinity);
L{f(x)} = 1/s^2-5*y/s;

Case 2: f(y) := x-5*y; (x exists parameter)

L{f(y)} = int(exp(-s*y)*f(y),y=0..infinity);
L{f(y)} = int(exp(-s*y)*(x-5*y),y=0..infinity);
L{f(y)} = x/s-5/s^2;

text:
int main()
{
   int age, feet, inches, pounds;
   string hair, eye;
}


int means integer, string is something like "brown", "mary had a little lamb", etc
you can also do char to define a letter varible, or char can be used as a string by declaring a character array.

